headline: Why Lockheed Martin Stock Flew Higher on Friday
summary: An analyst's price target bump was the news pushing shares of storied defense company Lockheed Martin (NYSE: LMT) skyward as the trading week came to an end.  Well before the market open, Matthew Akers of influential "big four" U.S. bank Wells Fargo raised his price target on Lockheed Martin to $476 per share, up from his previous $468.  Currently, through the leadership of the recently created Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE), the Trump administration has made moves to cut staffing and budgets at various federal agencies.

headline: Boeing Secures a Contract to Aid F/A-18 Jet Program for the Navy
summary: Boeing secures a $33.2 million contract to produce and deliver 41 DTP-N B Kits, five DTP-N B Kit Lab Assets and nine Processor eXpress Mezzanine Cards.
